<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-30T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-30T07:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3709: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-30T20:00:00+08:00">January 30, 1932—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 30—6:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my telegram of January 27, I have now decided that the
                            exigencies justify my requesting that the landing forces from American
                            vessels be increased at the earliest moment possible.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CES1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>